website_summaries.verdict: Product is sourced in the United States, containing high-quality proteins with no grains added.
pros: Delivers proteins from muscle and organs to ensure a safe recipe
Reasonable price for a freeze-dried cat food
Uses only products certified and inspected by the USDA and FDA
cons: Some issues with quality control in the manufacturing process

customer_reviews.title: QC needs improving.
customer_reviews.text: Found large (~2") piece of partially melted plastic fused into turkey pellets. Need better quality control. Could have been quite dangerous if swallowed.
customer_reviews.author: Bimbo Savant

customer_reviews.title: USDA human grade ingredients all sourced in USA with NO questionable/controversial ingredients
customer_reviews.text: I switched to Northwest Naturals after Stella & Chewy started adding Menadione Sodium Bisulfite Complex (MSBC) in all their freezed-dried cat food. You can read my comment regarding MSB at  I contacted Joslyn with Northwest Naturals who confirmed that all ingredients are sourced in the USA, are human grade and manufactured in a USDA facility. Nothing is sourced in China and there are no questionable or controversial ingredients! The switch was easy and both, the turkey & chicken, were rated A+ by my kitty.
customer_reviews.author: chouchou

customer_reviews.title: Best raw freeze-dried food out there
customer_reviews.text: My 17 yr old cat has a very sensitive stomach and can't handle any food with grains. He's also a very finicky eater so when he developed early stage kidney disease I wanted to switch to a raw diet but he wouldn't eat the frozen raw food. I tried several other brands of freeze dried but he wasn't interested until I gave him Northwest Naturals. Now he's right there at mealtime and gobbles it up. It is the easiest food I've tried to rehydrate, just use hot water for best results.
customer_reviews.author: Empress

customer_reviews.title: Love it!
customer_reviews.text: I bought this at my local pet store but oh gee how my cat eats this up! I hardly have a chance to rehydrate it before she's eating it. They have excellent customer service as I contacted them to find out the carb percentage in the chicken formula and they gave me the direct contact to their nutritionist! The percentage is 1%. This matters add I feed Scottish Folds and they require a low carb diet to maintain optimal joint health. I will continue to feed this superior food to my cat and her kittens.
customer_reviews.author: SeattleT

customer_reviews.title: Ferrets are crazy for this
customer_reviews.text: When I got this it was crushed completely, I thought it was a lost cause because I have only given my ferrets freeze dried foods whole. I tried to salvage it and I mixed in water and rehydrated the powder till it became clumpy and my ferrets are obsessed. I've never seen them more obsessed with anything in my life, not even their chicken heart snacks. I bought a second bag that didn't come crushed and I crush them into small pieces myself and rehydrate. This food is better than most freeze dried food because it has a simple ingredient list and has organ meat and bones mixed in, forever will be my favorite choice.
customer_reviews.author: Jess

customer_reviews.title: Quality change?
customer_reviews.text: Normally love this product but I don’t know if there was a change in the formulation, storage, etc, but while the texture is normally very soft and “fluffy” and easy to break apart, the last couple bags of the rabbit formula (red bag) have been exceptionally hard and difficult to crumble/rehydrate/soften. Wondering what changed and if this is a problem with the manufacture/formulation, or if it’s resulting from some other factor down the line. I receive a couple bags monthly they subscribe and save so I will give it another shot and see how the next month or two goes but if the quality does not improve I will be cancelling this order.
customer_reviews.author: Pen Name

customer_reviews.title: Cats do not like
customer_reviews.text: My cats (and I have 5, kind of scary) do not like it. They are interested, lick it a bit, maybe eat one, but if given a choice between this and their regular food (IAMS) they go for their regular food. Yea, I know can's can take a while to get used to new food but I figured they would be all over this like it was canned food (which they love). Also, it seems to make them vomit. And as others have noted, there is a lot of powder in the bag.
customer_reviews.author: Joe

customer_reviews.title: Trying to gradually move our 2 cats over to a ...
customer_reviews.text: Trying to gradually move our 2 cats over to a raw diet. One of our cats loves this with warm water. The other throws it up almost every time and we only give her 1 pellet mixed in with her regular processed food and a drop of warm water. Her stomach might just be too sensitive. But will try again at another time.
customer_reviews.author: Chris Chen

customer_reviews.title: Seems fine but cat can't eat it.
customer_reviews.text: This seemed like a good quality food but after a week our cat (one wouldn't eat it the other did) began to howl with stomach aches after eating then threw it up. Primal and Stella & Chewy began to have the same problem. We went back to canned wellness. He began vomiting the Primal first. Not sure if that triggered it or all rehydrated food does that.
customer_reviews.author: PAE

customer_reviews.title: Picky kitty loves it
customer_reviews.text: She loves this stuff and it has really made a difference in her litterbox odor from #2. The reason we got it for her was because she is apparently allergic to wheat which is in so many cat foods. It would cause bloody, horrible stools. But this has straightened her out. Only con is the price. Didn't freaking realize turkey was as expensive as gold flakes in Oregon. If you're able to afford this for your pet, it's a wonderful product.
customer_reviews.author: Dub

customer_reviews.title: Cats loved it
customer_reviews.text: Of my three cats, two were slightly skeptical at first, but did eventually eat it. After several meals all three were very ready for dinner time and licked their bowls clean. The only downside to the is the price, I realize quality ingredients drive up the price, but my goodness this stuff does not last long for three house cats. I will likely feed kibble and supplement with this.
customer_reviews.author: KT

customer_reviews.title: raw for cats
customer_reviews.text: This is a WONDERFUL product. My Cat Cuppy-Cake just Loves. Big believer cats need some "raw" in their diet. Convenient and feel its safer then buying raw chicken, turkey, etc. Per instructions I add freeze dried pellets to hot water. Let sit to hydrate. Squeeze out just some of the water, leave rest for it turns into broth. Break up with a fork and serve. Super healthy and give your bet the natural energy they need. Sometimes I'll mix in with Cuppy's wet food. Cuppy is 16 years old and now has much more energy than before. A Must Try. Have for dogs as well. kaszy Carlson
customer_reviews.author: Marianna Carlson

customer_reviews.title: mostly powdered...
customer_reviews.text: They were mostly powdered. Please make sure they are not...it is very hard for cats to eat like that even mixed with water.
customer_reviews.author: YF

customer_reviews.title: Ragdolls love this food!
customer_reviews.text: It took a couple of times of introducing this food to my ragdolls for them to eat it. Cats need food low in phosphorous without a lot of filler like carbs. Add water and make into a paste. I also mix with this with high protein canned cat food for a variety.
customer_reviews.author: Linda Denton

customer_reviews.title: My cats wouldn't even taste it.
customer_reviews.text: This food looks disgusting and the smell is nothing that might attract a cat to eat it. I have 3 cats and none of them would even taste it. Not after all a good buy for the price.
customer_reviews.author: Sammiesuesmom

customer_reviews.title: Good quality and quantity and My kitty loves it
customer_reviews.text: I have a picky cat, so I give him a combination of raw food and freezer dried food. I also switch up his freezer dried food so he doesn't get bored of it. I so far got the rabbit one, he absolutely loves it. I give it dry or as a topper, but I also have fountain for him, so giving it dry is not a problem, and he likes it dry too. The quality is really good and consistent, and it lasts long too.
customer_reviews.author: Sky.

customer_reviews.title: Cat couldn't eat it.
customer_reviews.text: This seemed like a good quality food but after a week our cat (one wouldn't eat it the other did) began to howl with stomach aches after eating then threw it up. Primal and Stella & Chewy began to have the same problem. We went back to canned wellness. He began vomiting the Primal first. Not sure if that triggered it or all rehydrated food does that.
customer_reviews.author: PAE

customer_reviews.title: Great Product...Rivals Stella and Chewys!
customer_reviews.text: My cats love Stella and Chewys(SC), but my wallet doesn’t. I stumbled across NORTHWEST NATURALS and my cats love it as much if not more than SC, and it’s much more affordable for me. I’m definitely going to start buying Northwest Naturals.
customer_reviews.author: Alicia

customer_reviews.title: My Ferrets go nuts for this stuff!
customer_reviews.text: Like the title said, my ferrets absolutely love this. I can't do a full raw food diet, so I buy freeze dried to supplement their kibble. They love the morsels of meat and I use the powder/flakes left to make soups for them and they DEVOUR it. Please keep these as low carb as possible Norwesth! Thank you!
customer_reviews.author: thepinupcowgirl

customer_reviews.title: Cats LOVE this product!
customer_reviews.text: Of course, I did not taste this item... but my cats are nuts for it. Yes, it will crumble a bit, because they are very light and delicate, but the cats do not notice and will gladly eat up the crumbs. Or, try putting the crumbs on dry or canned food, it is the taste they love, not the shape or texture.
customer_reviews.author: TWIGGY

customer_reviews.title: Don’t spend your money!
customer_reviews.text: I have no doubt that the product itself is amazing, as I have sued them in the past, BUT.... This product arrived to me basically in dust. Every freeze dried piece was pulverized, I bought this to put in my cat’s automatic feeder, and couldn’t just feed him dust. It’s one of those items that doesn’t ship well.
customer_reviews.author: Jackelyn

customer_reviews.title: Disappointed
customer_reviews.text: Very disappointed. It arrived all crumbled up and unusable. I suggest not buying it online.
customer_reviews.author: Dog Lover

customer_reviews.title: Visible difference in my kitty’s appearance
customer_reviews.text: I have been feeding this freeze dried cat food to my rescue kitty for about six months. She is about four years old. Her fur is rich and soft. I feed this along with a dry kibble that is available all day.
customer_reviews.author: Nancy H. Babbs

customer_reviews.title: The contents were crushed
customer_reviews.text: My cat loves this stuff but when the package arrived it was nothing but powdered bits. She wouldn't eat. I won't buy from this vendor again.
customer_reviews.author: Gretchen

customer_reviews.title: The most excellent cat food we've come across
customer_reviews.text: I can't thank you enough, NW Naturals, for helping to cure my cat of chronic, distressing diarrhea. Nothing I tried before helped until I read an obscure post from a "cat" website that mentioned this food had helped a cat with the same condition. The most excellent cat food we've come across.
customer_reviews.author: swissmoon

customer_reviews.title: Cat likes this food
customer_reviews.text: I have an IBD cat that mostly eats a different brand of freeze dried. I wanted to add a different protein not available in the other brand. She likes this food very well, but has had more loose stools than before I fed it to her. Also, the pieces are large except for the ones that crumble to a powder; maybe not an issue if I fed moist like you are supposed to , but my cat prefers it dry.
customer_reviews.author: cornspot

customer_reviews.title: These liver pellets taste really good!
customer_reviews.text: ... at least judging by how both our cats and dog go nuts for it. LOL the dog will eat any kind of freeze-dried liver but the cats prefer it soft and powdery. They won't eat tough liver treats.
customer_reviews.author: Dale's Cousin

customer_reviews.title: Cat loves it
customer_reviews.text: Very light because it's freeze dried and my cats seem to think they need to eat a lot more of it than the feeding instructions say. They do love the taste though and helped my cat with IBD
customer_reviews.author: Marianne Pirotta

customer_reviews.title: Good for freeze-dried option
customer_reviews.text: Needed a quick replacement for my cat who usually eats Primal. She liked it just fine and was way cheaper than some of the other freeze dried options on here.
customer_reviews.author: Sadie M

customer_reviews.title: Good
customer_reviews.text: My picky cat runs hot and cold on this stuff. When she is running hot, it will cause a slight decrease in her weight-that is a good thing as she is over weight. Also prefers it dry and not reconstituted.
customer_reviews.author: PeterG

customer_reviews.title: Northwest Naturals freeze dried Excellent product!
customer_reviews.text: My 3 kitties immediately began to eat as soon as I offered them their first nibble; I am thrilled! My kitties are quite fussy; now they are eating a truly healthy meal. Thank you NorthWest Naturals! Thank you Amazon for selling this product!
customer_reviews.author: Viva

customer_reviews.title: Keeps your cat young and healthy
customer_reviews.text: My cats love the chicken flavor of this freeze-dried raw food. And of course it’s very healthy for them. I only wish that it wasn’t so expensive!
customer_reviews.author: Carol B. Anderson

customer_reviews.title: Good Product !
customer_reviews.text: My cat is 16 years old and has no teeth left. Once this is re-hydrated it becomes so soft my cat can eat it with ease. She also love the taste. This is a bit expensive, as with any de-hydrated pet food, but worth it overall I buy this for my cat all the time, i just keep re-ordering the same thing

customer_reviews.title: 1/2 the food is crumbled and powdery instead of kibble
customer_reviews.text: I like other products by Northwest Naturals but this food is disappointing. First bag came and over 70% of the food was just powder. They replaced and 2nd bag was 50% powder. My cat will not eat the powder, so both bags going back.
customer_reviews.author: KathyK

customer_reviews.title: Lilly is doing really well w/this food
customer_reviews.text: My cat Lilly has not had a hairball for the 4 months she's been eating NW Turkey. Previously she had been having hairballs about twice a month. Was not expecting this, and am very happy I switched her from another brand freeze-dried chicken. I always rehydrate w/lots of water. She's a picky eater and I didn't have too many choices. I'm impressed with this product.

customer_reviews.title: Cats won't eat it

customer_reviews.title: all 4 cats ate it
customer_reviews.text: this does not happen very often, but all four of my cats ate this cat food, this speaks louder than my words

customer_reviews.title: Good for a Sensitive Tummy
customer_reviews.text: Our cat has food allergies to most preservatives, many vegetables and fish! So she mainly eats chicken and does enjoy the freeze dried along with a dry food. Cannot let it sit long after adding the warm water is the only complaint.

customer_reviews.title: So glad I discovered this high quality food!
customer_reviews.text: Excellent food and my cats love it! Easy to rehydrate or sprinkte on as a topper. Love the ingredients and that they are sourced in the US. Will definitely buy again.

customer_reviews.title: High five!
customer_reviews.text: The cats liked it right off the bat! Licked the bowls clean (I thought they were going to take the finish off the bowls!)

customer_reviews.title: Healthy food my cat loves!
customer_reviews.text: My picky wild cat loves the flavor. I put the dry, crumbles into her Nula dry food. Haven’t tried to wet yet.

customer_reviews.title: Easy to prepare, nutritious freeze dried raw diet.
customer_reviews.text: My cat loves this stuff, especially the turkey and chicken flavors. I feel the ingredients are appropriate for a healthy nutritious wet meal. I provide Northwest Naturals and a premium kibble from another provider, and my little guy finishes the Northwest Naturals first! It took about a week to get him used to the new texture and flavors, but it was worth it!

customer_reviews.title: Good product, poor packaging

My cats like this food but only in the dry form which means I paid a lot for a very little amount of useable food. My cats will not eat it rehydrated and so was pretty much a total bust for our household. If you are using this rehydrated then it wouldn't matter if the food came in chunks or powdered and rest assured that it is a very good product. I just wouldn't recommend buying it without being able to examine the package in person.

product_meta.title: Northwest Naturals Freeze Dried Raw Cat Food Nibbles, 11 Ounces
product_meta.description: Flavor Name:OtherWe use the same meats found at your finest natural food stores. All of our muscle and organ meats are chopped (not ground) partially frozen at the time of processing to ensure the availability of the highest quality nutrients, then individually quick frozen to keep the integrity of the ingredient quality. Our recipes are very simple, Chicken and Turkey Recipes use muscle meat, organ meats and natural raw ground bone, all from the same species. No added fruits or vegetables. A true carnivore diet! All products are produced in our own certified and inspected USDA, FDA, FSIS manufacturing facility. All poultry products are HPP'd for safety.
feature_bullets: 98% Highest Quality Turkey Muscle, Organ Meats And Bone
No Added Hormones, Antibiotics, Grains Or Fillers
Made And Sourced In The Usa
